  "body": "After installing `@openzeppelin/test-environment'` in the sample project, I am trying to run the following basic test:\r\n```\r\nconst { accounts, contract } = require('@openzeppelin/test-environment');\r\nconst [owner] = accounts;\r\n\r\nconst { expect } = require('chai');\r\n\r\nconst MyContract = contract.fromArtifact('Greeter');\r\n```\r\n\r\nI try to run with `npx hardhat test` and get\r\n```\r\n{ Error: /Users/amanusk/Code/Solidity/sample/build/contracts/Greeter.json: ENOENT: no such file or directory, open '/Users/amanusk/Code/Solidity/sample/build/contracts/Greeter.json'\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt seems I need to configure it somehow to search for the artifacts in the correct dir. Perhaps the dir structure is not what is expected\r\n\r\nAdding the configuration\r\n```\r\npaths: {\r\n    artifacts: './build/contracts',\r\n  },\r\n```\r\nIn hardhat.config.js also gives a similar error",
