    "body": "It seems like the artifacts convention that `@openzeppelin/test-environment` follows is the same as the one in truffle (and similar to the one used by buidler before). That is not the case in Hardhat (you can read about that [here](https://hardhat.org/guides/compile-contracts.html#artifacts)).\r\n\r\nFrom what I see in [their API](https://docs.openzeppelin.com/test-environment/0.1/api#contract), one alternative is doing this:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nconst GreeterArtifact = artifacts.readArtifactSync(\"Greeter\")\r\nconst Greeter = contract.fromABI(GreeterArtifact.abi)\r\n```\r\n\r\nI haven't tested it, but maybe that works. There's also a chance that you need to pass `GreeterArtifact.bytecode` or `GreeterArtifact.deployedBytecode` as the second argument, I'm not sure.",
